\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 She pointed over his shoulder, to an nearby patch of scrub brush, whose wild branches were clouded by a swarm of pinprick dots. It was a horde of tiny flies. There were so many that the noise of their zipping wings combined to sound something like a hissing snake.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Only Solraheen knows how many hook flies are over there,\u8221\'94 Moteah said. \u8220\'93Why are they over there? They can go anywhere\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 they can crawl into any hole, they can fly in every direction, they can explore the entire world and see things no hook fly has ever seen, but they don\u8217\'92t do it. They hover in that small bush. There\u8217\'92s a lot of bushes, but they\u8217\'92re all in that one. Why?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Tell me,\u8221\'94 Mandri said as he braced himself for a bit of folksy Outland wisdom.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Hook flies swarm like that because the most interesting thing in all the world is each other.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Like most figures of speech, Moteah\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s analogy had a surface charm that suggested a deeper truth, but it completely broke down upon further investigation. Humans weren\u8217\'92t like hook flies in any respect. There was a more prosaic reason those flies were flying around in a ball. There were more primal interests at play. Perhaps they\u8217\'92d found water there in that bush, or food, or the bush broke the breeze making it easier to fly in the first place. Most likely it was about sex; no doubt they bunched up into a cloud like that because it was the easiest way to bump their stiff little uglies into something that made them feel alive. Maybe one could say that still lines up with Moteah\u8217\'92s point, because humans are much the same, but Mandri didn\u8217\'92t get the feeling that\u8217\'92s what she meant.}
